<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5711465-andrew"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1309351240i/5711465._UX100_CR0,24,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5711465-andrew">Andrew</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Emma Messenger is good, I agree. But my own preference in the end is the light-stepping Eleanor Brun. She does have a british accent. But she knows ho<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Emma Messenger is good, I agree. But my own preference in the end is the light-stepping Eleanor Brun. She does have a british accent. But she knows how to quickly speak "desultory" and "indefatigable". Brun is subtle in her reading, and to me, Messenger adds too much drama, just a little too heavy on that pedal. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
