<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/767032-why-would-lily-consider-paying-back-all">Why would Lily consider paying back all the money she owed when she received her inheritance since that act would be ruinous to her? Seems she was brain dead or would she have been carted off to prison for non payment?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_767032'><a id="like_count_community_question_767032" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/767032?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F17728.The_House_of_Mirth">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/767032-why-would-lily-consider-paying-back-all">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/767032-why-would-lily-consider-paying-back-all">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/51986847-hayley"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/51986847-hayley">Hayley</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">She paid back all the money that she owed because her personal integrity wouldn&apos;t permit her to return to society with a debt like that still unpaid. <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">She paid back all the money that she owed because her personal integrity wouldn't permit her to return to society with a debt like that still unpaid. Also, there was the implication that Trenor at least expected some kind of "personal" favour in return for lending Lily money, and I can well imagine that anything she could do to avoid that prospect would also be high in her mind. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
